	(24033,89,'wpcf-short-description','An experimental prototype to visualize skateboarding tricks.'),
	(24034,89,'wpcf-long-description','Flow is an innovative way to look at skateboarding. Using a sensor attached to a skateboard, I am able to track the board\'s motion and visualize its movement in a 3D environment. The software takes the data input from the sensor and outputs a stylized recreation of the skater\'s run, transforming the position and orientation of the board into a visual breakdown of the steps involved in a trick. By displaying all these positions together, and in a 3D environment, skaters can now look at their tricks as a whole, from start to finish, seeing the trace of their tricks and how it flows.'),
