	(25490,532,'wpcf-short-description','A series of kits created to teach basic STEAM principles to marginal populations.'),
	(25491,532,'wpcf-long-description','STEAM Punks is a set of kits that allow for children in Kabul to explore technology and design through making. These electronic kits support the development of critical thinking skills, creativity, curiosity, and (most importantly) the drive to ask \"What if?\". \"What if?\" allows children to imagine and accomplish what might currently feel impossible. \r\n\r\nThese kits are a part of a complete ecosystem that aims to train teachers, support inquiry into design and technology, and promote learning through making. All kits have been developed taking into consideration the dominant language, local patterns and colors, as well as respect for ethnic backgrounds and political and religious taboos.'),
